title: The Mosqueto Indian and his golden river :being a familiar description of the Mosqueto Kingdom in America. With a true relation of the strange customs, ways of living, divinations, religion, drinking-bouts, wars, marriages, buryings, &c. of those heathenish people; together with an account of the product of their country
note: Detached from: A collection of voyages and travels ..., compiled by Awnsham and John Churchill (London, 1732), v. 6, p. [282]-298.
